rComments: Good teacher although material is long and can be tricky if you don't pay attention...was pretty clear and explanatory.
She's incredible.  Best professor I've ever had.  Those who dont understand that shouldn't be sitting in the lecture.  The book isnt to memorize either... its to help and it really does.

all i remember is the thinkness of the notes package. She was not clear on what she wanted from us; much extraneous information was provided that she never intedned to test us on. Memorization sucks; she expects us to remember details about stuff identified by cryptic 3 digit names

She was a good, straight-forward lecturer, though her slides could be toned down (there's a lot of distracting extra stuff she doesn't want you to know).  Her exam questions tested stupid concepts, "which one of the following is a dimer"?
Haphazard lecturer who doesn't bother giving any context for what she's saying.  Master of stating the obvious, and repeats herself ad nauseam.
Memorizing a phonebook's worth of material is not learning
